One of the top traditional rulers in Ondo State, the Olowo of Owo, Oba Folagbade Olateru-Olagbegi, died yesterday in his town at 77. Oba Folagbade, who was given the staff of office by the Late Governor Olusegun Agagu on December 11, 2003, was the eldest son of his. father, Sir Olateru Olagbegi. A lawyer by profession, the Late Oba Folagbade was appointed Chancellor of the University of Benin in 2005 and later Chancellor, University of Abuja. The late monarch celebrated his 15th anniversary on the throne in 2014. Until his demise, he was currently the Chancellor of University of Jos. He was married to Olori Ololade Olateru-Olagbegi and blessed with children and grandchildren. Meanwhile, the Olubadan of Ibadanland, Oba Saliu Adetunji, has described the late Olowo of Owo as a great man, even in death. Oba Adetunji said this in a statement by his Director of Media,Â  Adeola Oloko. He said the death of Olowo came as a rude shock to him, but noted that he lived an exemplary life worthy of emulation. He commiserated with the government and people of Ondo State in general and the people of Owo town and his immediate family in particular. Ondo traditional ruler, Olowo of Owo dies at 77 Olowo's death, a rude shock - Olubadan Mimiko increases stipends of traditional rulers